@Caroline AOSE Thank you for your comment, Caroline!  How do you think the number who enter undetected is estimated?  With very recent visits to the southern border by both current President Biden and former President Trump, this is certainly a major topic in the news.
A good source of information on migrants on the U.S.-Mexico border is the Pew Research Center. Check out their report “Migrant encounters at the U.S. Mexico border hit a record high at the end of 2023,” which includes many other graphs.

Come back on Friday when we publish the free link to the New York Times article that includes this graph.  You will learn details about additional aspects of this graph and be able to read the discussion about who thinks what when it comes to U.S. southern border crossings by migrants.

@Tara AOSE Thank you for your comment, Tara!  Since these are such big numbers, would it be helpful to think in terms of percentages?  Do you wonder what will happen to the 1.8 million in ongoing proceedings or legal limbo (about 58% of all attempted crossings)?
